# Rule: Environment Setup
SCOPE
- Ensure proper virtual environment and environment variable setup.

REQUIREMENTS
- Always activate virtual environment before running commands: .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
- Load .env file for environment variables in Python scripts.
- Use PowerShell syntax for all terminal commands.
- Install dependencies in virtual environment, not globally.

CONTEXT
- @reference cursorrules/index.mdc
- @reference pyproject.toml
- @reference .env (if exists)

COMMANDS
- Activation: .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
- Install: pip install -e .
- Run: python -m datastore.cli
- Test: python -c "import datastore; print('ok')"
